"Mieruch S., Noël S., Bovensmann H., Burrows J.P., Freund J.A.","Markov chain analysis of regional climates",2010,"Nonlinear Processes in Geophysics","17","6",,"651","661",,,10.5194/npg-17-651-2010,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78649390314&partnerID=40&md5=0e2dc85b93230ab9a901affde7b1e0f8","Institute of Environmental Physics (IUP), University of Bremen, Otto-Hahn Allee 1, 28359 Bremen, Germany; Institute for Chemistry and Biology of the Marine Environment (ICBM), University of Oldenburg, Carl-von-Ossietzky Str. 9-11, 26111 Oldenburg, Germany","Mieruch, S., Institute of Environmental Physics (IUP), University of Bremen, Otto-Hahn Allee 1, 28359 Bremen, Germany; Noël, S., Institute of Environmental Physics (IUP), University of Bremen, Otto-Hahn Allee 1, 28359 Bremen, Germany; Bovensmann, H., Institute of Environmental Physics (IUP), University of Bremen, Otto-Hahn Allee 1, 28359 Bremen, Germany; Burrows, J.P., Institute of Environmental Physics (IUP), University of Bremen, Otto-Hahn Allee 1, 28359 Bremen, Germany; Freund, J.A., Institute for Chemistry and Biology of the Marine Environment (ICBM), University of Oldenburg, Carl-von-Ossietzky Str. 9-11, 26111 Oldenburg, Germany","We present a novel method for regional climate classification that is based on coarse-grained categorical representations of multivariate climate anomalies and a subsequent Markov chain analysis. From the estimated transition matrix several descriptors, such as persistence, recurrence time and entropy, are derived. These descriptors characterise dynamic properties of regional climate anomalies and are connected with fundamental concepts from nonlinear physics like residence times, relaxation process and predictability. Such characteristics are useful for a comparative analysis of different climate regions and, in the context of global climate change, for a regime shift analysis. We apply the method to the bivariate set of water vapour and temperature anomalies of two regional climates, the Iberian Peninsula and the islands of Hawaii in the central Pacific Ocean. Through the Markov chain analysis and via the derived descriptors we find significant differences between the two climate regions. Since anomalies are departures from seasonal and long term components, these differences relate to differences in the short term stability of both regional climates. © 2010 Author(s).",,"climate classification; climatic region; estimation method; Markov chain; matrix; multivariate analysis; nonlinearity; regional climate; Hawaii [United States]; Iberian Peninsula; Pacific Ocean; Pacific Ocean (Central); United States",,,,,,"Andersson, A., Fennig, K., Klepp, C., Bakan, S., Graßl, H., Schulz, J., The hamburg ocean atmosphere parameters and fluxes from satellite data - HOAPS-3 (2010) Earth Syst. Sci. Data Discuss., 3, pp. 143-194. , doi:10.5194/essdd-3-143-2010; Beck, C., Grieser, J., Kottek, M., Rubel, F., Rudolf, B., Characterizing global climate change by means of köppen climate classification (2005) Klimastatusbericht, pp. 139-149; Blüthgen, J., Weischelt, W., (1980) Allgemeine Klimageographie, Walter de Gruyter, , German; Bovensmann, H., Burrows, J.P., Buchwitz, M., Frerick, J., Noël, S., Rozanov, V.V., Chance, K.V., Goede, A.H.P., SCIAMACHY-mission objectives and measurement modes (1999) J. Atmos. Sci., 56, pp. 127-150; Burrows, J.P., Schneider, W., Geary, J.C., Chance, K.V., Goede, A.P.H., Aarts, H.J.M., De Vries, J., Visser, H., Atmospheric remote sensing with SCIAMACHY (1990) Digest of Topical Meeting on Optical Remote Sensing of the Atmosphere, 4, pp. 71-74. , Optical Society of America, Washington; Burrows, J.P., Hölzle, E., Goede, A.P.H., Visser, H., Fricke, W., SCIAMACHY - Scanning imaging absorption spectrometer for atmospheric chartography (1995) Acta Astronaut., 35, pp. 445-451; Burrows, J.P., Weber, M., Buchwitz, M., Rozanov, V., Ladstätter- Weißenmayer, A., Richter, A., Beek, R., Perner, D., The global ozone monitoring experiment (GO